{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:matthew.14",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "matthew",
    "chapterNumber": 14,
    "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14",
    "summary": "Source text for Matthew 14 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.14.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14:1",
      "text": "At that time, Herod the tetrarch heard the report concerning Jesus,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.14.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14:2",
      "text": "and said to his servants, “ This is John the Baptizer. He is risen from the dead. That is why these powers work in him.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.14.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14:3",
      "text": "For Herod had arrested John, bound him, and put him in prison for the sake of Herodias, his brother Philip ’s wife.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.14.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14:4",
      "text": "For John said to him, “ It is not lawful for you to have her.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.14.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14:5",
      "text": "When he would have put him to death, he feared the multitude, because they counted him as a prophet.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.14.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14:6",
      "text": "But when Herod ’s birthday came, the daughter of Herodias danced among them and pleased Herod.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.14.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14:7",
      "text": "Therefore he promised with an oath to give her whatever she should ask.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.14.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14:8",
      "text": "She, being prompted by her mother, said, “ Give me here on a platter the head of John the Baptizer.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.14.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14:9",
      "text": "The king was grieved, but for the sake of his oaths and of those who sat at the table with him, he commanded it to be given,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.14.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14:10",
      "text": "and he sent and beheaded John in the prison.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.14.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14:11",
      "text": "His head was brought on a platter and given to the young lady; and she brought it to her mother.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.14.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14:12",
      "text": "His disciples came, took the body, and buried it. Then they went and told Jesus.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.14.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14:13",
      "text": "Now when Jesus heard this, he withdrew from there in a boat to a deserted place apart. When the multitudes heard it, they followed him on foot from the cities.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.14.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14:14",
      "text": "Jesus went out, and he saw a great multitude. He had compassion on them and healed their sick.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.14.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14:15",
      "text": "When evening had come, his disciples came to him, saying, “ This place is deserted, and the hour is already late. Send the multitudes away, that they may go into the villages, and buy themselves food.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.14.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14:16",
      "text": "But Jesus said to them, “ They don’ t need to go away. You give them something to eat.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.14.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14:17",
      "text": "They told him, “ We only have here five loaves and two fish.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.14.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14:18",
      "text": "He said, “ Bring them here to me.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.14.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14:19",
      "text": "He commanded the multitudes to sit down on the grass; and he took the five loaves and the two fish, and looking up to heaven, he blessed, broke and gave the loaves to the disciples; and the disciples gave to the multitudes.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.14.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14:20",
      "text": "They all ate and were filled. They took up twelve baskets full of that which remained left over from the broken pieces.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.14.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14:21",
      "text": "Those who ate were about five thousand men, in addition to women and children.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.14.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14:22",
      "text": "Immediately Jesus made the disciples get into the boat and go ahead of him to the other side, while he sent the multitudes away.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.14.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14:23",
      "text": "After he had sent the multitudes away, he went up into the mountain by himself to pray. When evening had come, he was there alone.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.14.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14:24",
      "text": "But the boat was now in the middle of the sea, distressed by the waves, for the wind was contrary.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.14.25",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14:25",
      "text": "In the fourth watch of the night, Jesus came to them, walking on the sea.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.14.26",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14:26",
      "text": "When the disciples saw him walking on the sea, they were troubled, saying, “ It ’s a ghost!” and they cried out for fear.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.14.27",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14:27",
      "text": "But immediately Jesus spoke to them, saying, “Cheer up! It is I! Don’t be afraid.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.14.28",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14:28",
      "text": "Peter answered him and said, “ Lord, if it is you, command me to come to you on the waters.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.14.29",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14:29",
      "text": "He said, “ Come!” Peter stepped down from the boat and walked on the waters to come to Jesus.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.14.30",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14:30",
      "text": "But when he saw that the wind was strong, he was afraid, and beginning to sink, he cried out, saying, “ Lord, save me!”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.14.31",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14:31",
      "text": "Immediately Jesus stretched out his hand, took hold of him, and said to him, “ You of little faith, why did you doubt?”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.14.32",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14:32",
      "text": "When they got up into the boat, the wind ceased.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.14.33",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14:33",
      "text": "Those who were in the boat came and worshiped him, saying, “ You are truly the Son of God!”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.14.34",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14:34",
      "text": "When they had crossed over, they came to the land of Gennesaret.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.14.35",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14:35",
      "text": "When the people of that place recognized him, they sent into all that surrounding region and brought to him all who were sick;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:matthew.14.36",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "matthew",
      "chapterNumber": 14,
      "verseNumber": 36,
      "referenceLabel": "Matthew 14:36",
      "text": "and they begged him that they might just touch the fringe of his garment. As many as touched it were made whole.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
